.TH KINDLETOOL 1 "July 2026" "KindleTool 2.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kindletool \- create, inspect, convert, and safely extract Kindle update packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kindletool
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Rust KindleTool is compatible with the v1.6.6 package formats and command surface. It
recognizes FB01, FB02, FB03, FC02, FC04, FD03, FD04, FL01, SP01, CB01, gzip, and ZIP headers.
Package fields are decoded explicitly as little-endian values and untrusted archive paths are
confined to the requested extraction directory.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B md [input] [output]
Apply the Kindle byte substitution. A missing path or a single dash selects standard input or output.
.TP
.B dm [input] [output]
Reverse the Kindle byte substitution.
.TP
.B convert [options] input...
Inspect or convert one or more packages. File-mode conversion deletes each source only after a
validated, flushed, atomic output succeeds. Use
.B -k
to keep sources or
.B -c
to write payloads to standard output and always keep sources. Other modes are
.BR -i " (information), " -s " (SP01 signature), " -u " (stored payload), and " -w
(remove one SP01 envelope).
.TP
.B extract [-u] input output
Validate the complete decoded update archive in private staging and atomically commit it to an
absent or empty output directory.
.TP
.B create type [options] input... [output]
Create an ota, ota2, recovery, recovery2, or signed userdata package. A single .tar.gz, .tgz,
or .tar input is treated as a prebuilt archive. A missing output or a single dash selects staged
standard output. Run
.B kindletool help create
for all generated device and format choices.
.TP
.B info serial
Print the model and derived root/recovery passwords for a 16-character serial number.
.TP
.B version
Print version information.
.TP
.B help [command]
Print general or command-specific help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 indicates success, 1 an execution failure, and 2 a command-line usage failure.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KT_WITH_UNKNOWN_DEVCODES
Expose data-mined device identifiers in aliases and numeric diagnostic output.
.TP
.B KT_PKG_METADATA_DUMP
Write shell-friendly parsed package metadata to this path.
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Select temporary spooling storage.
.SH SAFETY
Extraction rejects absolute paths, parent traversal, duplicate paths, escaping symbolic or hard
links, unsupported entries, and manifest mismatches. Output files and extraction directories are
staged, flushed, validated, and committed only on success.
.SH COMPATIBILITY
Version 2.0 retains the v1.6.6/1.7 command interface. Its breaking changes are limited to the Rust
library API. The C v1.6.6 implementation remains the differential-test oracle.
